The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses clustering and Gaussian Mixture Models, which are topics related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for patch searching, which involves selecting the best similar patches for denoising, indicating a focus on optimization and algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) possible sub-categories.
